1- In terminal for frontend/client run--->npm i -g firebase-tools (maybe need to add sudo at start of command)
2-firebase login
to login with another email use--> firebase logout then firebase login

3-firebase init
spacebar to select
steps:
Hosting: Configure files for Firebase Hosting and (optionally) set up GitHub
Action deploys

? Select a default Firebase project for this directory: (Use arrow keys)

> challenge-12345 (amazon-challenge)---> unique id

Use an existing project

What do you want to use as your public directory? (public)--->write---> build

? Configure as a single-page app (rewrite all urls to /index.html)? (y/N) type yes by def no

4-npm run build---->bundle the app in a tiny efficent package to deploy (create build folder)

5- firebase deploy--->goe to built folder and find content and deploy it.

hosting url:
https://challenge-12345.web.app
